          <p>Traditional merchant accounts offer the lowest base rates but lack integration capabilities that cost HVAC companies an average of 22 minutes per transaction in manual data entry. Companies processing over $75,000 monthly should evaluate traditional processors, while smaller operations benefit more from integrated solutions despite slightly higher rates.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="my-8">
        <h2 id="jobber-payments" class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Jobber Payments Review</h2>
        
        <div class="prose max-w-none">
          <p><a href="https://go.getjobber.com/bo42cjptz4m2" rel="sponsored nofollow">Jobber Payments</a> processes over $2.1 billion annually for field service companies, with HVAC contractors representing their largest user segment. The system integrates directly with Jobber's CRM, eliminating the need for separate payment terminals or manual invoice matching.</p>

          <p>Key advantages for HVAC companies include same-day ACH processing (available next business day), automatic payment reconciliation, and mobile card readers that work offline during service calls. Jobber's fraud detection reduces chargebacks by 31% compared to standalone processors, saving companies an average of $340 annually in dispute fees.</p>

          <p>The platform supports all major card types, Apple Pay, Google Pay, and bank transfers. Processing rates start at 2.4% for swiped transactions, competitive with traditional processors while offering significantly better integration. Companies using <a href="/hvac/pricing/jobber-pricing">Jobber's full platform</a> save an estimated 3.2 hours weekly on payment-related tasks.</p>

          <div style="background: #E8F4FD; border-left: 4px solid #2563EB; padding: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
            <p style="margin: 0;"><strong>Real Cost Example:</strong> ABC Heating (8 trucks) processed $840,000 through Jobber Payments in 2025, paying $20,736 in fees (2.47% effective rate). Their previous setup with Square + manual entry cost $21,840 in fees plus 12 hours weekly of administrative work valued at $7,800 annually.</p>
          </div>

          <p>Jobber Payments requires using Jobber as your primary CRM, making it unsuitable for companies committed to other platforms. However, for businesses already using or considering <a href="/hvac/crm/jobber-vs-servicetitan">Jobber versus ServiceTitan</a>, the integrated payment processing provides substantial operational benefits beyond rate savings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="my-8">
        <h2 id="housecall-pro-payments" class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Housecall Pro Payments</h2>
        
