      <div class="my-8">
        <h2 id="implementation-guide" class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Implementation Guide</h2>
        
        <div class="prose max-w-none">
          <p>Successful payment processing implementation requires careful planning to minimize disruption during the transition period. HVAC companies should plan for 2-4 weeks implementation time for integrated solutions and 4-8 weeks for custom integrations.</p>

          <p>Start by auditing current payment workflows and identifying integration requirements. Companies processing over 500 transactions monthly should implement during slower seasons to work through any technical issues without impacting peak revenue periods.</p>

          <p>For businesses choosing Jobber or Housecall Pro, payment processing setup occurs during CRM onboarding. Both platforms offer migration assistance and training for technicians and office staff. Expect 2-3 days of reduced efficiency as teams adapt to new workflows.</p>

          <p>Square and Stripe implementations require coordination between your HVAC CRM vendor, payment processor, and any integration middleware. Test all workflows thoroughly in a sandbox environment before processing live transactions. Budget for potential integration fixes during the first 30 days of operation.</p>

          <div style="background: #F3E8FF; border-left: 4px solid #7C3AED; padding: 1rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
            <p style="margin: 0;"><strong>Implementation Checklist:</strong> Verify PCI compliance requirements, train all payment-handling staff, update customer communication templates, test offline payment scenarios, and establish backup payment methods for system downtime. Have your previous processor on standby for 30 days in case of implementation issues.</p>
          </div>

          <p>Consider running parallel systems for 1-2 weeks during transition, processing some payments through the new system while maintaining your existing setup. This approach reduces risk while allowing real-world testing of integration workflows and staff training.</p>
